## Part 7: Anti-Patterns

### 1. Redundant Tool Documentation
❌ Tool description + prompt section + inline mentions all explaining same tool
✅ Tool description = HOW, prompt = WHEN (reference only)

### 2. Verbose Inline Examples
❌ Multiple code examples showing similar concepts
✅ One canonical example OR external `technicalResources` reference

### 3. Prescriptive Step Lists
❌ "1. Analyze 2. Understand 3. Fix 4. Verify" (obvious sequence)
✅ "Fix incrementally, verify after changes"

### 4. Defensive Over-explanation
❌ "IMPORTANT: You MUST always... NEVER forget to... CRITICAL:..."
✅ State once, trust model capability

### 5. Static Tool Overload
❌ Loading all 50 tool definitions in every request
✅ Dynamic tool discovery based on task intent

### 6. Context Hoarding
❌ Keeping all conversation history indefinitely
✅ Sliding windows with summarization for older content

